    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-09-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-09-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="869"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d869">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Tower</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">St. Petersburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-09-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 17, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 601.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    the unnumbered dispatch of Mr. Adee, Acting Secretory of State, dated the 12th
                    of August, 1902, in which he inclosed to me your circular letter<note n="a"
                        xml:id="d869fna">Printed under Austria, p 42.</note> dated <pb facs="1017"
                        n="937" xml:id="pg_937"/> the 11th of August, in regard to the condition of
                    Jews in Roumania, with two additional printed copies of that letter.</p>
                <p>In compliance with your instructions I sought an interview with Count Lamsdorff,
                    Imperial Russian minister for foreign affairs, to whom I presented the subject,
                    and to whom, upon his request, I handed one of the printed copies of your
                    circular letter.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charlemagne Tower.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
